===Noun===
'''scorn''' (''uncountable'')

# [[Contempt]] or [[disdain]] towards a [[despicable]] or [[unworthy]] person

====Quotations====
*'''circa 1605''': The cry is still 'They come': our castle's strength / Will laugh a siege to '''scorn''' &mdash; ''[[w:William Shakespeare|William Shakespeare]], [[w:Macbeth|Macbeth]]''
*'''1968???''': Rain of tears, real, mist of imagined '''scorn''' &mdash; John Berryman, ''Berryman's Sonnets''

